title: CheckboxWidget (wikitext Mode)

!! Wikitext Inline Mode

<<.from-version "5.4.0">>

TiddlyWiki supports an inline checkbox syntax directly in wikitext, similar to GitHub Flavored Markdown:

```
[ ] Unchecked task
[x] Checked task
[X] Also checked (uppercase X)
```

When rendered, each `[ ]`/`[x]`/`[X]` becomes an interactive checkbox. Clicking it directly modifies the `text` field of the //source tiddler// — the tiddler whose wikitext was parsed — replacing the checkbox syntax in-place.

!!! Behaviour inside transclusions

When a tiddler containing inline checkboxes is transcluded with `{{OtherTiddler}}`, clicking a checkbox will update //OtherTiddler//, not the tiddler that contains the transclusion. This is the correct behaviour: the source of truth is always the tiddler that owns the text.

!!! Combining with list syntax

Inline checkboxes integrate naturally with the TiddlyWiki list syntax:

```
* [ ] Bullet list item
* [x] Done
# [ ] Numbered item
** [ ] Nested item
```

Bullet list items whose first element is a checkbox will have their list marker hidden via CSS, producing a clean task-list appearance.

!!! Filter operator

The [[checkbox Operator]] can be used to find tiddlers by checkbox state:

```
[all[tiddlers]checkbox[unchecked]]
```

Returns all tiddlers that have at least one unchecked checkbox.

!!! Example

<<wikitext-example-without-html """* [ ] Buy milk
* [x] Write code
* [ ] Ship feature""">>
